section.section:
The regulations adopted under paragraph (1) of this subsection shall include requirements that ignition interlock systems:
Do not impede the safe operation of the vehicle;
Minimize opportunities to be bypassed;
Correlate accurately with established measures of blood alcohol levels;
Work accurately and reliably in an unsupervised environment;
Require a proper and accurate measure of blood alcohol levels;
Are installed in a tamper proof manner and provide evidence of attempted tampering;
Are difficult to circumvent, and require premeditation to circumvent;
Minimize inconvenience to a sober user;
Are manufactured by a party responsible for installation, user training, service, and maintenance;
Operate reliably over the range of motor vehicle environments or motor vehicle manufacturing standards;
Are manufactured by a person who is adequately insured for products liability;
Provide the option for an electronic log of the driver's experience with the system; and
Are certified by a qualified laboratory approved by the Administration.
